Okay here's the deal, I have a 4 stroke 75 horse Merc and according to the Merc web site it is identical (near as I can tell) to the 90 horse in every detail. So the question is how do I, or can I tap into the extra 15 horse?  75 EFI FourStroke Specifications  90 EFI FourStroke Specifications
might be a different carb and manifold    multi-port  Injection...so maybe not....LOL
It's electronic fuel injected (EFI) Terry. I'm thinking it's a computer module type thing.
You edit to fast.
Could be Cams and timing or Comp module
yup, I was thinking old school  you can buy different chips for trucks that can change the hp , so why not
http://continuouswave.com/ubb/Forum1/HTML/014043.html  heres a link i found if you feel like doing some reading
Different cams,injectors,intake manifold,exhaust manifold,timing,spark plugs,cylinder heads and ECM.
